## 4. State Management

The application uses a **hybrid approach** — there is no Redux or centralized state store for application data. Instead:

### localStorage (Primary Persistence)

| Key | Data | Lifecycle |
|---|---|---|
| `access_token` | JWT string | Set on login, cleared on 401 or sign-out |
| `user_profile` | `{ emp_no, name, dept, grade }` | Set on login, read by Sidebar/ChatOverlay/Timesheet |
| `access_tree` | Module/collection/agent hierarchy | Set on login, refreshed on dashboard mount |
| `lightMode` | `'true'` / `'false'` | Toggled by sidebar theme switch, persisted |
| `sidebarCollapsed` | `'true'` / `'false'` | Toggled by sidebar collapse button, persisted |

### useChatStream Hook (Chat-Specific State)

The [useChatStream.js](src/hooks/useChatStream.js) hook manages all chat-related state internally:

| State | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `messages` | `Array<{role, content, isTyping, type, formSpec, formErrors, isSubmitted, isSubmitting, isCancelled, isError, attachedFiles, ...}>` | Full conversation thread with inline form renders, file attachments, and error states |
| `isStreaming` | `boolean` | Global streaming lock — disables input, shows spinner |
| `threadIdRef` | `MutableRefObject<string | null>` | Current conversation thread ID, auto-set from SSE `meta` events |
| `isStreamingRef` | `MutableRefObject<boolean>` | Synchronous lock to prevent double-submission race conditions ("Double-Submit Ghost" fix) |
| `abortControllerRef` | `MutableRefObject<AbortController | null>` | User-initiated stream cancellation |

#### SSE Event Types Handled

| `parsed.type` | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `meta` | Extracts `thread_id` → stored in `threadIdRef.current` for session continuity |
| `chunk` | Appends `text` to `fullReply`, updates last message's `content` with streamed text |
| `form_widget` | Replaces last message with `type: 'form'`, sets `formSpec` from `parsed.form` |
| `form_errors` | Sets `formErrors` on the form message at `msgIndex`, shows validation error text |
| Error in `parsed.error` | Throws the error message for handling in catch block |

#### Error Handling

| HTTP Status | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `401` | Clears all auth keys, redirects to `/` |
| `403` | Attempts permission re-sync via `refreshAccess()`, shows access-denied toast |
| `400` | Throws "Malformed request or unknown module" |
| `AbortError` | Silently logs "Stream stopped by user" — no error displayed |
| Other non-2xx | Catches `response.json().detail` or falls back to HTTP status code |

### React Router Outlet Context (Parent-to-Child Communication)

[DashboardLayout.jsx](src/layouts/DashboardLayout.jsx) provides state to child routes via React Router context:

```jsx
<Outlet context={{ openChat, activeCollection, setActiveCollection }} />
```

- **`openChat(collectionName)`** — Opens the ChatOverlay full-screen slide-in panel.
- **`activeCollection`** / **`setActiveCollection`** — Tracks which module/collection is currently active for chat routing.
- Chat state is reset when navigating away from a chat-opened page.

