### Dark/Light Mode Implementation

**Theme toggle mechanism:**
1. Sidebar theme toggle button (Sun/Moon icon when collapsed, labeled switch when expanded)
2. On click: reads `localStorage.getItem('lightMode')` → toggles `document.body.classList.toggle('light-mode')`
3. State persisted in `localStorage.lightMode`
4. Transition: `body` has `@apply transition-colors duration-500` for smooth 500ms theme switch

**Two-layer approach:**
- **Custom `@layer components`** — Uses `.light-mode` descendant selectors (e.g., `.light-mode .login-box`)
- **Tailwind `dark:` prefix** — Used directly in JSX (e.g., `dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200`) — works independently of the `light-mode` class via the `darkMode: 'class'` config

### No CSS-in-JS or CSS Modules

Despite `@emotion/react`, `@emotion/styled`, `@mui/material`, Ant Design, PrimeReact, React Bootstrap being installed in `package.json`, **none are used** in the codebase. All styling is pure Tailwind utility classes with custom component definitions via `@layer components`.

